42
00:02:30,375 --> 00:02:31,875
Girl: Happy New Year!
You, too.

43
00:02:31,958 --> 00:02:33,458
Boy: I was cramming
all through --

44
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:35,208
Boy #2: I think I'm gonna try
for an easier school.

45
00:02:35,291 --> 00:02:36,458
Girl #2:
I missed you!

46
00:02:36,541 --> 00:02:37,875
Girl #3: I heard he got
early admission.

47
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:39,541
Boy #3:
Must be nice.

48
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:41,958
[ Girl giggles ]

49
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:44,333
Read them and weep!
B again!

50
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:46,375
-Love, right?
-Got to be love.

51
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,166
Girl #4:
No doubt about it.

52
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:51,750
Tsubaki:<i> See what you can do</i>
<i>when you put your mind to it?</i>

53
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:54,791
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>
<i>I should go tell him!</i>

54
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:56,083
[ Door sliding open ]

55
00:02:56,166 --> 00:02:57,916
Oh, Kousei?

56
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:12,458
Aww.

57
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:15,833
Hey!

58
00:03:17,666 --> 00:03:19,416
Not today, buddy.
Come here.

59
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,166
The lovely Kaori requests
your presence within.

60
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:23,750
Kousei: I'm just gonna be
the third wheel.

61
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:26,208
This is a horrible idea,
Watari.

62
00:03:26,291 --> 00:03:28,416
Happy New Year!

63
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,291
Right back at you!

64
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:34,583
You know, just because you
squeaked through the prelims

65
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:36,250
doesn't mean you can rest
on your laurels,

66
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:37,666
and waste time
at the hospital!

67
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,500
Go home and practice,
you slacker!

68
00:03:39,583 --> 00:03:42,250
Kousei:
You're the one that told me
to stop by in the first place.

69
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:43,708
Watari: Remember that kid
I mentioned?

70
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:45,083
Mm-hmm.

71
00:03:45,166 --> 00:03:46,458
They're sending her off
to an all-girls school.

72
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:48,625
I'd totally go to
a school like that.

73
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:50,083
You'd have to wear
the uniform.

74
00:03:50,166 --> 00:03:51,791
We could be roomies,
partners in crime.

75
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:55,291
Yeah -- till they kick
both of us out.

76
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:57,541
[ Dramatic music plays ]

77
00:03:57,625 --> 00:04:00,291
Tsubaki:<i> She's totally</i>
<i>interested in Watari.</i>

78
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:04,375
Kaori:<i> [ Laughs ]</i>
<i>Watari!</i>

79
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:07,791
Kousei:<i> The girl who likes</i>
<i>my best friend.</i>

80
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:11,250
<i>I'm just a third wheel,</i>
<i>and a stand-in,</i>

81
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:13,666
<i>and a pack mule,</i>

82
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:16,708
<i>and her accompanist</i>
<i>all too briefly.</i>

83
00:04:16,791 --> 00:04:20,166
<i>But I'm not Watari.</i>

84
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,500
[ Cicadas chirping ]

85
00:04:21,583 --> 00:04:24,000
Hey, are you sure?

86
00:04:24,083 --> 00:04:26,333
I don't think your mom's
gonna like it.

87
00:04:26,416 --> 00:04:27,875
That just means
I'll have to do

88
00:04:27,958 --> 00:04:29,791
whatever it takes
to keep her.

89
00:04:29,875 --> 00:04:33,125
How could Mom say "no"
to something this cute?

90
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:35,291
It's gonna be fine.

91
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:40,000
[ Dramatic music plays ]

92
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:41,833
[breathing heavily]

93
00:04:41,916 --> 00:04:48,291
♪♪

94
00:04:48,375 --> 00:04:50,500
[ Breathing heavily ]

95
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:59,083
♪♪

96
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:00,750
Tsubaki: Drink it.

97
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,541
You're gonna catch a cold
if you don't warm up, Kousei.

98
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:05,791
I've been looking
for Chelsea everywhere,

99
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:09,666
but she's not at the junkyard
or under the bridge.

100
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:12,208
She's gonna freeze to death
out in the rain.

101
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:14,208
She's just
a little kitten!

102
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:16,416
I let my mom
take her away,

103
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:19,500
even though I knew she'd
never give Chelsea back.

104
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:21,875
But I thought, if I
could find her out here,

105
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:23,833
at least I'd know
she was alright!

106
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:25,625
Girl:
<i>He's his mother's puppet.</i>

107
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:27,875
Boy:
<i>The human metronome.</i>

108
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:30,208
Kousei: It's true what
they say about me!

109
00:05:30,291 --> 00:05:32,666
I'm a soulless puppet
my mom created

110
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:36,375
because she can't play
the piano anymore!

111
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:38,875
[ Crying ]

112
00:05:38,958 --> 00:05:40,250
Shows what you know.

113
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:43,708
I bet your soul is
all kinds of shiny.

114
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:45,000
Seriously, Kousei.

115
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:46,583
You're a lot
of good things.

116
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:48,333
You've just got to
remember them.

117
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:51,875
Yeah, like the way...
uh...

118
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:55,750
Well, like the way
you're out here

119
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,666
looking for Chelsea
in the rain.

120
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:00,208
It's 'cause you feel bad
about what happened to her.

121
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:04,250
Puppets wouldn't feel
that kind of stuff, right?

122
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:07,041
See, Kousei?
You do, too, have a soul.

123
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:09,083
It's just that you
put it away somewhere,

124
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:13,291
and now, you don't remember
exactly where it is.

125
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:16,708
That's why I'll find
your soul for you.

126
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:23,375
It'll be a big job,
and it might take me a while.

127
00:06:23,458 --> 00:06:25,541
Even after we find it,

128
00:06:25,625 --> 00:06:27,750
I'll stay with you
forever and ever.

129
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,458
How's that sound?

130
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,375
[ Rain pattering ]

131
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:36,833
Going to the hospital?
-Yeah.

132
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:38,791
She demands that I check in
with her a bunch,

133
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:41,708
then yells at me for not
using the time to practice.

134
00:06:41,791 --> 00:06:43,208
I can't win.

135
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:50,625
Watari.

136
00:06:50,708 --> 00:06:53,708
I bet you he's heading over
to see Kaori, too.

137
00:06:53,791 --> 00:06:58,291
Actually,
I think it's gonna rain.

138
00:06:58,375 --> 00:07:00,208
Let's go another day.

139
00:07:03,125 --> 00:07:04,875
<i>It does smell rainy.</i>

140
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:13,833
Oh?

141
00:07:13,916 --> 00:07:15,291
Check it out, Kousei.

142
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:17,333
You called it.

143
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:22,000
[ Dramatic music plays ]

144
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:27,916
♪♪

145
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,291
Here.
You read my mind.

146
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:33,500
Now, if you could just
turn this all into snow.

147
00:07:33,583 --> 00:07:35,291
Yeah, 'cause trudging
to school through it

148
00:07:35,375 --> 00:07:38,041
is so much fun.

149
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:39,375
Pour some syrup
into it,

150
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:41,875
and you can make
your own shaved ice.

151
00:07:41,958 --> 00:07:44,000
If people weren't weird
about yellow snow,

152
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:46,375
we could use
that lemonade.

153
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:48,666
<i>We're just</i>
<i>like always --</i>

154
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:53,250
<i>making silly jokes,</i>
<i>hiding out from the rain.</i>

155
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:55,208
I like your handkerchief,
Tsubaki.

156
00:07:55,291 --> 00:07:56,375
It's cute.

157
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:59,000
<i>The two of us,</i>
<i>him and me.</i>

158
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:01,916
It's pretty girly,
but you are a girl.

159
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:05,916
<i>You're a human.</i>
<i>A human girl.</i>

160
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,416
<i>I guess you're a girl</i>
<i>after all, huh?</i>

161
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,833
<i>You liar.</i>

162
00:08:09,916 --> 00:08:13,333
♪♪

163
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:17,208
I know why you backed out
on going to see Kaori.

164
00:08:17,291 --> 00:08:19,333
It's 'cause
of Watari.

165
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:22,958
Kousei: No. It looked rainy.
That's all.

166
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,541
You're lying.

167
00:08:24,625 --> 00:08:26,791
♪♪

168
00:08:26,875 --> 00:08:29,541
Honestly, I didn't want
to get in the way

169
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:31,041
if they had the chance
to be alone.

170
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:32,583
Just stop it!

171
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:35,041
The only reason we're here
is 'cause watching them laugh

172
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:38,000
and have fun,
it tears you up inside!

173
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:41,666
♪♪

174
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,000
<i>That's why you avoid her.</i>

175
00:08:44,083 --> 00:08:47,458
Kousei:<i> I can tell right away</i>
<i>when you're holding back.</i>

176
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:49,916
<i>You think you can keep it</i>
<i>all bottled up,</i>

177
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
<i>but I've always known</i>
<i>what's in your heart.</i>

178
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,458
<i>I can read you like a big,</i>
<i>dumb book.</i>

179
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:58,250
♪♪

180
00:08:58,333 --> 00:08:59,666
You love Kaori.

181
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,833
You've loved her
all along.

182
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:06,791
Kaori:
<i>Miwa told me something.</i>

183
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:08,500
<i>The moment I</i>
<i>laid eyes on him,</i>

184
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:10,750
<i>my old life</i>
<i>just blew away.</i>

185
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:14,166
<i>Everything I saw and heard,</i>
<i>everything I felt,</i>

186
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:16,000
<i>the world around me</i>
<i>took on color</i>

187
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:18,666
<i>in a way</i>
<i>I never knew it could.</i>

188
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:21,958
<i>It began to sparkle.</i>

189
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:23,875
<i>You're Friend A!</i>

190
00:09:26,208 --> 00:09:28,791
Mm-hmm.

191
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:30,416
[ Rain pattering ]

192
00:09:41,625 --> 00:09:43,666
Well, it's not
gonna happen, okay?

193
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:46,125
Kaori's all head over heels
for Watari.

194
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:47,833
Always has been,
dummy.

195
00:09:47,916 --> 00:09:50,416
As if she'd ever give you
a second look.

196
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:53,208
Yeah, I know.

197
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:55,000
When it comes to girls,
you're not gonna beat him.

198
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:58,000
Next to him,
they wouldn't even see you.

199
00:09:58,083 --> 00:10:00,000
You're right.

200
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:01,875
<i>You liar.</i>

201
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:03,958
<i>You told me</i>
<i>you'd stay with me.</i>

202
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:07,666
Kousei:<i> I can tell right away</i>
<i>when you're holding back.</i>

203
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:10,166
<i>You've known me forever,</i>
<i>but you can't tell</i>

204
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,833
<i>what I'm feeling,</i>
<i>can you?</i>

205
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:15,083
<i>I'm not even a girl</i>
<i>to you, huh?</i>

206
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:17,291
<i>You've never</i>
<i>seen me as one.</i>

207
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:21,666
[ Somber music plays ]

208
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:24,083
Stop acting
like a moron.

209
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:28,875
Kaori likes him.
That's just how it is.

210
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:31,958
♪♪

211
00:10:32,041 --> 00:10:33,458
[ Exhales ]

212
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:38,458
Maybe...

213
00:10:41,125 --> 00:10:44,375
You should fall in love
with me instead.

214
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:48,916
[ Dramatic music plays ]

215
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:57,833
♪♪

216
00:10:57,916 --> 00:10:59,833
Whatever, you dummy!

217
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:02,708
<i>See, Kousei?</i>
<i>That's what truth sounds like.</i>

218
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:06,041
<i>It was scary, but at least</i>
<i>he gets the picture, now,</i>

219
00:11:06,125 --> 00:11:07,375
<i>that I'm a girl.</i>

220
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:10,375
<i>It took a lot of tears</i>
<i>to get here.</i>

221
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:12,416
<i>Bet you he's crying, too --</i>

222
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,666
<i>not 'cause of his feelings,</i>

223
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:16,875
<i>but because I kicked him</i>
<i>so hard.</i>

224
00:11:16,958 --> 00:11:18,583
<i>He knows.</i>

225
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:20,500
<i>I told him.</i>

226
00:11:20,583 --> 00:11:23,750
<i>But what happens now?</i>

227
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:26,458
<i>My heart's</i>
<i>a mile a minute.</i>

228
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:31,625
<i>The rain feels so good,</i>
<i>and it tastes like lemonade.</i>

229
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:37,250
<i>I was frozen before,</i>
<i>but I just started to thaw.</i>

230
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:45,083
[ Gasps ]

231
00:11:45,166 --> 00:11:46,791
Hey, Tsubaki.

232
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,416
Kashiwagi: Thanks for
waiting.

233
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:56,333
[ Somber music plays ]

234
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:58,291
[ Baseball bat clinks ]

235
00:11:58,375 --> 00:12:02,625
♪♪

236
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:05,291
Look, you have a cold,
and I'm tired.

237
00:12:05,375 --> 00:12:06,708
Let's call it
a day, yeah?

238
00:12:06,791 --> 00:12:08,500
[ Coughing ]

239
00:12:08,583 --> 00:12:10,291
I just got rained on
a bit.

240
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:13,375
Now, keep those
pitches coming.

241
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:15,375
Fine.

242
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:17,916
But you're bringing them
all back from now on.

243
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,875
If that's what
I got to do.

244
00:12:19,958 --> 00:12:30,500
♪♪

245
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:41,166
♪♪

246
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,041
Something happen
with you and Arima?

247
00:12:43,125 --> 00:12:44,333
[ Gasps, shouts ]

248
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:46,083
[ Screams ]

249
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,833
[ Clattering ]

250
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:51,291
Are you trying to
knock my head off?
What the hell?

251
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:53,833
You can't just say stuff
like that mid-pitch!

252
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:56,083
Come on.
I wasn't born yesterday.

253
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:58,708
Each ball is landing
by the music room.

254
00:12:58,791 --> 00:13:00,708
You're fighting again.
Am I right?

255
00:13:00,791 --> 00:13:02,083
No.

256
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:04,333
Though I did kick him
in the leg pretty hard,

257
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:05,500
I guess.

258
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:06,750
Now that I
think about it,

259
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:08,416
he was limping
a little.

260
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,333
Hey, I didn't want to
talk about it

261
00:13:10,416 --> 00:13:11,625
in the first place, okay?

262
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,583
I just wanted to hit
some balls around!

263
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:15,916
You are officially
on my bad list!

264
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,375
Suffer, Kashiwagi!

265
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:20,958
<i>Not my fault you're</i>
<i>crazy for him.</i>

266
00:13:21,041 --> 00:13:23,708
<i>Now that you know</i>
<i>I'm a girl, Kousei,</i>

267
00:13:23,791 --> 00:13:25,000
<i>think of me.</i>

268
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:26,916
[ Baseball bat clinks ]

269
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,750
<i>Reach him.</i>
<i>Reach him.</i>

270
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:32,541
<i>You can do it!</i>

271
00:13:32,625 --> 00:13:40,541
♪♪

272
00:13:40,625 --> 00:13:44,041
<i>You should fall in love</i>
<i>with me instead.</i>

273
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:47,875
Kousei:<i> I mean,</i>
<i>what was that even about?</i>

274
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:50,208
<i>She was just</i>
<i>messing around.</i>

275
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:54,000
<i>But Tsubaki doesn't</i>
<i>joke like that.</i>

276
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,500
Tsubaki:<i> It's like having</i>
<i>a hopeless kid brother.</i>

277
00:13:56,583 --> 00:13:58,250
Kousei:
<i>Girls are weird --</i>

278
00:13:58,333 --> 00:14:01,583
<i>even the ones</i>
<i>you've known forever.</i>

279
00:14:01,666 --> 00:14:03,583
[ Ominous moaning ]

280
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:04,916
Woman:
Focus, damn it!

281
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,583
You've got to get your head
in the game, pal!

282
00:14:06,666 --> 00:14:10,041
The finals were in February,
for crying out loud!

283
00:14:10,125 --> 00:14:11,750
Sorry about that.

284
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,916
I'd like to say that
he's ahead of the pack,

285
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,375
but I'd be lying.

286
00:14:15,458 --> 00:14:17,083
His head is
in the back?

287
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,291
Listen to me.

288
00:14:18,375 --> 00:14:19,583
You'll be pitting
your skills against

289
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,458
the top young pianists
in Japan.

290
00:14:21,541 --> 00:14:23,625
Whether you're going on
to high school here,

291
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:25,458
or bugging out
for Europe,

292
00:14:25,541 --> 00:14:28,583
this competition
will decide your future.

293
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:30,083
It's time to sack up.

294
00:14:30,166 --> 00:14:32,416
You're playing in
the big leagues now.

295
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,500
Kaori:<i> I'm releasing you</i>
<i>from visit duty.</i>

296
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:38,833
Huh?

297
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:40,625
<i>The finals are right</i>
<i>around the corner.</i>

298
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:42,375
<i>Time for you to put every</i>
<i>spare moment into practice.</i>

299
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,125
<i>An hour here,</i>
<i>an hour there,</i>

300
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:45,708
<i>it adds up.</i>

301
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:47,416
<i>Anyway, I got to go.</i>

302
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:48,708
<i>Talk to you later!</i>

303
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:50,541
[ Phone receiver clicks ]

304
00:14:50,625 --> 00:14:52,458
[ Phone beeping ]

305
00:14:52,541 --> 00:14:53,958
[ Groans ]

306
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,416
What is her problem?

307
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,625
First she
demands I visit,

308
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:57,958
then she gives me
crap about it,

309
00:14:58,041 --> 00:14:59,625
and now, she tells me
not to bother!

310
00:14:59,708 --> 00:15:01,333
Which is it, tyrant?!

311
00:15:03,541 --> 00:15:06,875
Kousei:<i> Maybe it was</i>
<i>something I did.</i>

312
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:10,541
<i>I knew I shouldn't have eaten</i>
<i>her caneles that one time.</i>

313
00:15:10,625 --> 00:15:13,958
<i>And I definitely don't talk</i>
<i>enough while I'm there.</i>

314
00:15:14,041 --> 00:15:17,541
<i>She might still be steamed</i>
<i>about the Nagi thing, too.</i>

315
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:26,041
<i>If I don't see her</i>
<i>in the hospital,</i>

316
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:29,125
<i>does that mean I won't get</i>
<i>a chance to see her at all?</i>

317
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:31,041
[ Cellphone ringing]
[shouts]

318
00:15:31,125 --> 00:15:33,875
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

319
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:35,500
[ Cellphone beeps ]
You again?

320
00:15:35,583 --> 00:15:37,833
Kaori: I looked out the window,
and saw this huge plane.

321
00:15:37,916 --> 00:15:39,291
I wonder where
it's going?

322
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:40,958
<i>Cool, huh?</i>

323
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:42,416
Huh?

324
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:46,500
Yeah, there it goes.

325
00:15:46,583 --> 00:15:48,750
Kaori:<i> Hold on.</i>
<i>You can see it, too?</i>

326
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:52,333
<i>Wow, I guess we're under</i>
<i>the same sky.</i>

327
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:55,291
Is that why you called?

328
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:59,000
<i>Yeah.</i>
<i>Is that okay?</i>

329
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:02,875
[ Laughing ]

330
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:07,041
<i>The plane set sail</i>
<i>across an ocean of stars.</i>

331
00:16:07,125 --> 00:16:11,500
<i>Like a cat in the dark,</i>
<i>you appear out of nowhere.</i>

332
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:13,708
You told me not to come
to the hospital.

333
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:15,916
<i>It doesn't mean I'm not</i>
<i>gonna call, silly.</i>

334
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,541
<i>I had to share that plane</i>
<i>with someone.</i>

335
00:16:18,625 --> 00:16:20,750
<i>Just when I'm sure</i>
<i>she's through with me,</i>

336
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:24,583
<i>there she is, beckoning</i>
<i>for me to follow her.</i>

337
00:16:24,666 --> 00:16:26,625
<i>Same as I've always done.</i>

338
00:16:26,708 --> 00:16:28,375
I'll stop in
to see you.

339
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:29,958
You really
don't have to.

340
00:16:30,041 --> 00:16:32,375
It'd be different
if you had the time, but --

341
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,250
I don't care
about time.

342
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:37,208
[ Dramatic music plays ]

343
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:40,250
♪♪

344
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,083
I want to see you.

345
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:46,250
♪♪

346
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:50,208
<i>It flies overhead</i>
<i>as though by magic.</i>

347
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:52,875
<i>Knowing I'm under</i>
<i>the same sky as you,</i>

348
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:56,916
<i>it paints the night</i>
<i>with a touch of wonder.</i>

349
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,791
<i>You speak, and I swing</i>
<i>between hope and despair,</i>

350
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:04,708
<i>keeping time to the melody</i>
<i>in my heart.</i>

351
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:08,083
<i>What do people call</i>
<i>this feeling, again?</i>

352
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:12,916
<i>Something so rare</i>
<i>must have a name.</i>

353
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:16,750
<i>Maybe they call it</i>
<i>"being in love."</i>

354
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,125
That okay?

355
00:17:18,208 --> 00:17:23,458
<i>Even if they don't,</i>
<i>I know I do.</i>

356
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:25,125
Watari: I got the school thing
figured out.

357
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:26,750
Kousei: Oh, yeah?
How'd you do it?

358
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,625
One of them offered me
a soccer scholarship,

359
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:30,458
so I took the bait.

360
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:33,291
They told me to start
hitting up practice in March.

361
00:17:33,375 --> 00:17:35,250
Bottom of the heap
again, man.

362
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:38,541
Circle of life.

363
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,458
Still surprised
you came with.

364
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:44,041
When I'd ask before,
you'd always weasel out of it.

365
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:45,833
It wasn't you.

366
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:49,958
<i>I'm no Watari.</i>

367
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:53,291
<i>I'm the first to admit it.</i>
<i>But it still hurts.</i>

368
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:54,625
Tsubaki:
<i>You love Kaori.</i>

369
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:56,291
<i>You've loved her</i>
<i>all along.</i>

370
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:59,833
Kaori:<i> You see?</i>
<i>You're just yourself.</i>

371
00:17:59,916 --> 00:18:01,916
Hey, Watari.

372
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,833
♪♪

373
00:18:06,916 --> 00:18:10,833
I like Kaori --
like, a lot.

374
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:19,875
♪♪

375
00:18:19,958 --> 00:18:23,458
Well, yeah.
Of course you do.

376
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:27,500
[ Laughs ]

377
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:28,875
So, are we gonna duke it out
for her, or what?

378
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:31,166
Nurse: Get the doctor
in here now!

379
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,750
That's Kaori's room.

380
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,000
Just hang on.

381
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:35,791
The doctor's on his way.
Kaori, can you hear me?

382
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:38,125
Nurse #2:
Take a deep breath, Kaori.
That's a good girl.

383
00:18:38,208 --> 00:18:39,458
Deep breaths.

384
00:18:39,541 --> 00:18:40,875
Nurse #3: We need the doctor
in here! Find him!

385
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:43,041
Kaori!
Look at me!

386
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:45,166
Damn it,
she's seizing up!

387
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:46,500
Patient is coding!

388
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:49,291
You have to keep
your eyes open, Kaori!

389
00:18:49,375 --> 00:18:50,750
Kaori!

390
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:56,958
Doctor:
You can't be here right now.

391
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:58,208
Go home, boys.

392
00:18:58,291 --> 00:18:59,541
We'll take
good care of her.

393
00:18:59,625 --> 00:19:02,666
[ Dramatic music plays ]

394
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:19,083
♪♪

395
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:21,375
[ Tires squealing ]

396
00:19:24,625 --> 00:19:26,375
[ Tires squealing ]

397
00:19:29,791 --> 00:19:32,083
[ Breathing heavily ]

398
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:37,916
♪♪

399
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,083
Kousei: Hello?!

400
00:19:39,166 --> 00:19:41,916
Please open up!
I need help!

401
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,416
[ Gasping ]

402
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:50,791
♪♪

403
00:19:50,875 --> 00:19:54,375
Doctor: Prep it for X-ray,
and check its blood type.

404
00:19:54,458 --> 00:20:05,041
♪♪

405
00:20:05,125 --> 00:20:06,625
I wish I could have
done more,

406
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:10,791
but with injuries that bad,
they're beyond help.

407
00:20:10,875 --> 00:20:12,041
I'm sorry.

408
00:20:12,125 --> 00:20:13,750
Thank you
for trying.

409
00:20:15,916 --> 00:20:17,333
Are you okay?

410
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:20,625
Yeah.

411
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:22,625
[ Distant dog barking ]

412
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:34,541
[ Water running ]

413
00:20:42,125 --> 00:20:44,666
[ Water running ]

414
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:47,791
Kaori:<i> Do you think</i>
<i>you can just forget it?</i>

415
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:49,791
<i>You should come along.</i>

416
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:52,875
<i>Your hand is ready</i>
<i>to jump out of its skin.</i>

417
00:20:58,708 --> 00:21:00,625
<i>I'm glad it was you.</i>

418
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,541
[ Crying ]

419
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:20,416
[ Screams ]

420
00:21:22,375 --> 00:21:30,875
[ Singing in Japanese ]

421
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:40,125
[ Singing continues ]

422
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:55,250
♪♪

423
00:21:55,333 --> 00:22:06,500
♪♪

424
00:22:06,583 --> 00:22:17,750
♪♪

425
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:28,958
♪♪

426
00:22:29,041 --> 00:22:40,250
♪♪

427
00:22:40,333 --> 00:22:51,625
♪♪

